news.title: Forest department, MCG raze four dozen illegal farmhouses in Gurugram
news.para: On Wednesday, a team of the forest department led by Range Officer Karambir Malik and MCG's Assistant Engineer (Enforcement) Sanjog Sharma reached the Gwal Pahari area with three earthmovers and razed the illegal structures.

news.title: Companies try to lure workers back to desk with treehouses, garden plots
news.para: Some companies say nature-centered amenities have won them over. And some workers find the outdoorsy vibe reassuring.

news.title: Brickwork Ratings revises Macrotech Developers' credit rating upwards
news.para: The rating upgrade factors in the positive developments with respect to implementation of the plans envisaged and efforts of Macrotech Developers to gain traction in the warehousing segment through land monetization, Brickwork Ratings said.

news.title: Homebuyers can clear Greater Noida development body's dues till Sept 30
news.para: According to GNIDA’s records, there are 3,369 homebuyers and 217 plot owners who have defaulted on payments. They are from sectors 3, Omicron 1, 1A and 2, Xu 2 and 3, Mu 2, Eta 2, Alpha, Beta, Delta and so on.

news.title: Gurugram: HSVP seeks to recover Rs 372 crore from owners of plots, flats
news.para: The notices have been issued to group housing societies in sectors 43 and 52 and individual plots owners in sectors 27, 28, 42, 43, 51, 52 and 57. HSVP has threatened to take legal action and impose a penalty of 10% of the pending dues on the defaulters if they fail to pay up at the earliest.

news.title: Bail when buyers' money returns from abroad, SC tells Unitech promoters
news.para: According to the report, three subsidiaries of Unitech, between 2007-2010, invested Rs 1,745.81 crore in 10 companies in Cyprus. It further added that Rs 1,406.33 crore or 80 per cent of the total investment value, between 2016-18, was written off, while Rs 339 crore is appearing as equity investments in the books of accounts.

news.title: SC allows Unitech Group sub-panel to negotiate claims with three ARCs
news.para: The top court also permitted the sub-committee to hold negotiations with Noida and Greater Noida authorities, which has raised objections to the resolution plan presented by the new board, about the dues and the amount payable by the Unitech Group.

news.title: China Evergrande's supplier threatens lawsuit over late payment
news.para: Financial markets are worried that the size of Evergrande's debts present a systemic risk were it to fail and the firm's executives last week were issued a rare warning from regulators to get their house in order.

news.title: Kanpur's Z Square Mall sealed over Rs 13 crore unpaid property tax
news.para: ​KMC's Zonal Officer Rajesh Kumar Gupta told PTI that the shopping mall was sealed for not paying the civic body's dues of Rs 13,36,24,712 that comprises property tax of Rs 10,44,88,848 and the interest of Rs 2,91,35,864.

news.title: Delhi: SDMC not to disconnect water, power connections to unauthorised colonies
news.para: The civic body also directed officials to take back previous orders of disconnecting water and electricity connections in such colonies. A proposal in this connection was approved in the House meeting of the South Delhi Municipal Corporation (SDMC) on Wednesday.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Town planning adalat sees fewer applicants
news.para: ​The town planning adalats had always put the officials in a fix since many of the applications would be put off owing to deviation from norms or because of the fact that permits would be sought in violation of zoning norms or completion certificate sought for constructions done in violation of building rules.

news.title: Tamil Nadu to have six more corporations, 28 municipalities
news.para: Urban Development Minister K.N. Nehru made the announcement in the Assembly in his response to the debate on demands for grants for his department in the assembly.

news.title: Mohali development body takes online route to issue LoI for Aerotropolis project
news.para: The letter of intent will be delivered digitally as an SMS containing the link from where it can be downloaded, said Gmada chief administrator Pradeep Kumar Agrawal.

news.title: Bengaluru: Nadaprabhu Kempegowda layout allottees worried about basic amenities
news.para: A 30x40 sq ft site owner to pay Rs 60,000 fine if not building home 5 years after allotment. Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout allottees wanted to construct dream homes but could not do so as there was neither electricity nor water supply or UGD at the layout.

news.title: Karnataka CM hints at separate municipal corporation for Dharwad
news.para: A delegation of eminent citizens of Dharwad met Bommai at his residence in Hubballi during his visit to the city on Sunday and submitted a memorandum seeking bifurcation of HDMC.
